1. *Niže* drveće je trava visoka. (Below the trees, the grass is tall.)
2. Pogledaj *niže*, tamo se nalazi reka. (Look down, there is a river down there.)
3. *Niže* cene privlače mnoge kupce. (Lower prices attract many buyers.)
4. Ovaj red knjiga ide *niže* od prethodnog. (This row of books goes lower than the previous one.)
5. Idemo *niže* ulicom do kraja. (We're going down the street to the end.)
6. Stajao je *niže* od svih u redu. (He stood lower than everyone in line.)
7. Planine su *niže* od oblaka. (Mountains are lower than clouds.)
8. Svetlo se gasi *niže* po hodniku. (The light is turning off lower down the hallway.)

Note: The word "niže" in Serbian can have different meanings depending on the context in which it is used. It can mean "below," "down," "lower," "less," and "later."